Work tracker history items are already clickable with detail view

**Feature Status**: ALREADY IMPLEMENTED ✓

The requested functionality already exists in WorkTrackerView.swift:

1. **Clickable History Items** (CompactEntryRow):
   - `.onTapGesture { onTap() }` - Makes entire row clickable
   - `.onHover { hovering in isHovering = hovering }` - Hover effects
   - `.help("Click to view details")` - Tooltip on hover
   - Blue border appears when hovering
   - Background opacity changes to indicate interactivity

2. **Selection State** (RecentHistorySection):
   - `@State private var selectedEntry: TrackerEntry?` - Tracks selection
   - `onTap: { selectedEntry = entry }` - Sets selection on click
   - `.sheet(item: $selectedEntry) { entry in EntryDetailSheet(entry: entry, vm: vm) }` - Shows detail sheet

3. **Detail Sheet** (EntryDetailSheet):
   - Entry type badge with icon and color
   - Full raw text content
   - Category (if present)
   - Duration in minutes (if present)
   - Due date with relative time (if present)
   - Estimated time (if present)
   - Complete metadata (created/updated timestamps, entry ID)
   - Delete functionality with confirmation dialog
   - 500×600 sheet with scroll support

